properties.name: caesar_instruction
properties.content:
1. Wash and chop lettuce into bite-sized pieces.
2. Grate Parmesan cheese.
3. Prepare croutons by toasting bread cubes in olive oil until golden brown.
4. In a small bowl, whisk together olive oil, lemon juice, Dijon mustard, minced garlic, Worcestershire sauce, salt, and pepper to make the dressing.
5. Toss lettuce with dressing until evenly coated.
6. Add grated Parmesan cheese and croutons to the salad.
7. Serve immediately.
